Turkish Equity Movers: Emlak Konut, Garanti, Sabanci Are Active

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-03-04T13:24:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/turkish-equity-movers-emlak-konut-garanti-sabanci-are-active.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  rose 752.23, or 1.3 percent, to 61,139.27 at 3:21 p.m. in
Istanbul.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.    Emlak Konut Gayrimenkul Yatirim Ortakligi AS (EKGYO)  ,
Turkey’s largest housing developer, added 4 kurus, or 1.6
percent, to 2.62 liras. The company will buy property in
Istanbul from its parent, the government housing agency known as
Toki, for 225.4 million liras ($141 million), Emlak Konut said
in a statement to the exchange after the close yesterday.    Turkiye Garanti Bankasi AS (GARAN)  , the bank in which
Spain’s Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA is buying a 24.9
stake, increased 6 kurus, or 0.9 percent, to 7.12 liras. Garanti
will propose a gross dividend of 0.13571 lira per share, equal
to 0.11536 lira net, at a shareholders’ meeting on March 31, it
said in a statement to the bourse after the close yesterday.    Haci Omer Sabanci Holding AS (SAHOL)  , Turkey’s second
biggest group of companies, gained the most since July 2009,
adding 48 kurus, or 7.5 percent, to 6.92 liras. Exsa Export
Sanayi Mamulleri Satis & Arastirma AS, its foreign trade unit,
plans to buy a stake of as much as 5 percent in Sabanci Holding
on the bourse within a year, Exsa said in a statement to the
exchange yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
